  sodium: 490 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-spicy-lemon-maple-tofu-651c18348e598ea2ad62cf0c
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Open and drain @tofu{1}; press out excess water with paper towels. Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat and cut into ½-inch cubes.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Place tofu in a #large bowl{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add half the @cornstarch{2%tablespoon} and toss until evenly coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tofu in a single layer and cook until golden and crispy, ~{1-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Wipe out pan.

> For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil per batch.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together remaining cornstarch and @water{2%tablespoon}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for tofu over medium-low heat. Add garlic and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in cornstarch mixture, @maple syrup{2%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat.

> If sauce seems too thick, add splashes of water.

Return fried tofu to pan and toss until coated in sauce.

Divide rice between bowls; top with broccoli and tofu in separate sections.

Top broccoli with a pinch of @lemon zest{pinch} and sprinkle tofu with as many remaining chili flakes as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges if desired.